CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 14, 1967, pg. 3B reads: "Guests came to the Harrises' "open house" from many cities and states including the groom's two brothers. Seater, Raymond Sanderlin, Washington teacher; Terri Cuff, formerly of new Jersey and now teaching in Washington and far right the handsome host, Dr. Woody Harris, son of the hosts; Hampton Gee and the groom Dr. Willis E. Sanderlin. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated from left: Raymond Sanderlin, Terri Cuff, and Dr. Woodford "Woody" Alvin Harris; standing: Bernard Sanderlin, Mike Harris, Hampton Gee, and Dr. Willis E. Sanderlin, posed in Harris's home during open house party, Ambridge
